Cibyl is an environment to compile and run programs written in C,
Objective-C, C++ and possibly Fortran on J2ME phones. It is documented
on the project page at

http://cibyl.googlecode.com

Prerequisites
-------------
You need the following to use Cibyl:

- Python (2.3, 2.4 tested)
- The Jasmin assembler (http://jasmin.sourceforge.net)
- A GCC MIPS cross-compiler, >= 3.3
- A Java compiler / runtime environment
- The jasmin java assembler (jasmin.sourceforge.net)
- The Sun Wireless Toolkit for J2ME support

Setting up Cibyl
----------------
To setup Cibyl, do the following steps:

1. Edit env.sh and correct the paths there

2. Run

   $ source env.sh

   to setup the environment variables

3. Run

   $ make

   To compile Cibyl header files

4. Build the examples by running

   $ cd examples
   $ make

5. Run the examples by

   $ cd examples/sokoban
   $ make run

